<TITLE> Train hits rickshaw: 2 injured </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July (bdnews24.com)A mother and daughter sustained serious injuries Tuesday when the rickshaw they were travelling on was struck by a train at the Karwan Bazar rail-crossing in the city, police said. The accident took place at around midday when the Mymensingh-bound Balaka train struck the rickshaw as it was attempting to cross the rail lines while the barrier was down, Nazrul Islam, assistant sub-inspector of railway police, told bdnews24.com. Twenty-six-year-old Smriti Akhtar and her daughter Tarassum Akhtar, a student of class four, were taken to the National Institute of Trauma and Orthopedic Rehabilitation, popularly known as Pongu Hospital, after receiving first aid at a local clinic, police said. Smriti Akhtar remains in a critical condition and is yet to regain consciousness, while her daughter sustained an injury to her hand, said Md Asaduzzaman, assistant sub-inspector of Tejgaon Police Station. Police have been attempting to contact their relatives in the Begunbari area of the city. b
